| ID | Invariant | Source Reference | Plan Failure To Look For |
|---|---|---|---|

Examples of Plan Failure To Look For:

- missing gate
- hidden dependency
- ambiguous ownership
- milestone can close without preserving invariant
- future agent forced to decide architecture
- duplicated authority across plan and milestone specs

## Capability Integrity Rules

Define how the reviewer should protect capability meaning.

| ID | Capability / Rule | Integrity Requirement | Weak Plan Pattern |
|---|---|---|---|

Weak Plan Pattern should describe how a plan might appear to deliver the capability while leaving the intended capability incomplete, fragmented, duplicated, or semantically wrong.

## Authority Boundaries

Define artifact authority expectations relevant to adversarial review.

| ID | Authority Boundary | Correct Ownership | Drift / Duplication Risk |
|---|---|---|---|

